menu "breadboard: bb_log"

config BB_LOG_ROUTES
    bool "Build bb_log HTTP routes (SSE stream + log-level GET/POST)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_log compiles the routes module that exposes
        GET /api/logs (SSE stream), GET /api/logs/status, GET /api/log/level,
        POST /api/log/level. Adds bb_http, bb_json, and bb_registry to
        bb_log's PRIV_REQUIRES. Disable for headless logging-only consumers.

config BB_LOG_STREAM_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-init bb_log_stream via bb_registry early tier"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_log_stream_init is automatically invoked by
        bb_registry_init_early() without explicit app_main call.
        Disable to manually call bb_log_stream_init(). Independent of
        CONFIG_BB_LOG_ROUTES (stream capture vs. HTTP routes).

config BB_LOG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    bool "Capture log tail to RTC RAM for panic diagnosis"
    default y
    help
        Mirrors bb_log_stream output to RTC slow memory so the last
        few KB of log lines survive a software reboot. Exposed via
        GET /api/panic on the next boot if the previous boot was
        abnormal (panic, watchdog, brownout). Costs CONFIG_BB_LOG_PANIC_BUF_SIZE
        bytes of RTC slow memory.

config BB_LOG_PANIC_BUF_SIZE
    int "Panic log RTC buffer size (bytes)"
    default 2048
    range 512 8192
    depends on BB_LOG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    help
        Size of the circular buffer in RTC slow memory. Must fit in
        the chip's RTC slow memory budget (~8KB on ESP32-S3, less on
        smaller chips). 2 KB captures roughly the last 30-50 log lines.

config BB_LOG_PANIC_COREDUMP
    bool "Capture ESP-IDF coredump for panic backtraces"
    default n
    depends on BB_LOG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    help
        On panic, ESP-IDF writes a coredump to a dedicated flash partition.
        On the next boot, bb_log_panic decodes it via esp_core_dump_get_summary
        and exposes the task name, exception PC, and backtrace via
        GET /api/diag/panic. Requires a "coredump" partition entry in the
        consumer's partitions.csv (see examples/smoke/partitions.*.csv for
        the 64 KB layout). Also requires the following in sdkconfig.defaults:
            CONFIG_ESP_COREDUMP_ENABLE_TO_FLASH=y
            CONFIG_ESP_COREDUMP_DATA_FORMAT_ELF=y
            CONFIG_ESP_COREDUMP_CHECKSUM_CRC32=y
        Disabled by default to avoid forcing the partition change on existing
        consumers.

endmenu
